Consider replacing inline style with data-progress attribute and CSS custom property:

<div class="h-full rounded-[10px]" data-progress="<?php echo ( $current_page / $total_pages ) * 100; ?>"></div>

Then in Search.css:
.search-pagination-progress [data-progress] {
	width: calc(var(--progress, 0) * 1%);
	background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--color-neon-green), var(--color-blue));
}

And set CSS variable via inline style or JS:
style="--progress: <?php echo ( $current_page / $total_pages ) * 100; ?>"

This is more semantic than inline background and width styles, but the current implementation is acceptable.
